TY  - JOUR
T1  - Real-Time Delay Estimation in Overloaded Multiserver Queues with Abandonments
AU  - Ibrahim, Rouba
AU  - Whitt, Ward
Y1  - 2009/07/20
PY  - 2009
DA  - 2009/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.1090.1041
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.1090.1041
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1729
EP  - 1742
VL  - 55
IS  - 10
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - We use heavy-traffic limits and computer simulation to study the performance of alternative real-time delay estimators in the overloaded GI/GI/s+GI multiserver queueing model, allowing customer abandonment. These delay estimates may be used to make delay announcements in call centers and related service systems. We characterize performance by the expected mean squared error in steady state. We exploit established approximations for performance measures with a nonexponential abandonment-time distribution to obtain new delay estimators that effectively cope with nonexponential abandonment-time distributions.
AB  - We use heavy-traffic limits and computer simulation to study the performance of alternative real-time delay estimators in the overloaded GI/GI/s+GI multiserver queueing model, allowing customer abandonment. These delay estimates may be used to make delay announcements in call centers and related service systems. We characterize performance by the expected mean squared error in steady state. We exploit established approximations for performance measures with a nonexponential abandonment-time distribution to obtain new delay estimators that effectively cope with nonexponential abandonment-time distributions.
